snippet.textDisplay:
Now that Valentine's day is gone and some of us are still single and kiss-less, I decided to write a sad romantic poem about the Cermet...*ahem*

Kermit/Cermet is Crying

Once, in a house, on a warm LA day....
Some doggies were splooting,
and sleeping away.
There was Marble, and Peach,
And of course there was Bunny,
But something was off...
Indeed, something was funny...
Then out of the shower, the Cermet did trot,
With sad on his face...
like a poor depressed thot.
Jenna started to wonder,
"What could cause such a thing?"
Then suddenly realized....
They were out of Irish Spring!
The small Cermet cries grew louder, and louder,
Like a nasty-boi cloud of reverse sleeping powder.
Then after a while the Cermet did bellow,
There was no saving nap time....
It lost all it's mellow.
Cermet cried in hysterics,
He just couldn't cope....
He longed for "The Spring"....
He yearned for "The Soap".
